In large, heavy saucepan, cook beef with onion and green pepper until meat is brown, stirring frequently. Drain off any fat. Add tomatoes; break into chunks. Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper until well mixed. Stir in beans and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in cereal and cook about 10 minutes longer, stirring frequently.